-- Canada Increases 5-Year Funding for Maternal Health Plan by C$1.1 Billion
-- Theophilos Argitis
-- 2010-06-25T19:34:21Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-25/canada-increases-5-year-funding-for-maternal-health-plan-by-c-1-1-billion.html

          
          
             Canadian Prime Minister Stephen
Harper announced his government will increase funding for
maternal and child health programs in poor countries by C$1.1
billion ($1.06 billion) over five years, bringing its total
committment over that time to C$2.85 billion.  
 Harper, who is chairing a meeting of Group of Eight leaders
today in Huntsville, Ontario, also pledged to make the
committment “permanent and long-term” beyond the five-year
period, according to a statement issued today by his office.  
